Freight wagons for transporting basic foods produced 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 4 (KCNA) -- New type freight wagons for transporting basic foods were produced at the June 4 rolling-stock factory.
 They are equipped with all the facilities necessary for transporting basic foods including bean paste and soy sauce. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 These foods will be supplied to units of the Korean People's Army and people in different parts of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Modern factories have been built in various parts of the country in recent years to produce basic foods including bean paste, soy sauce and oil.

Arms buildup in S. Korea denounced 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 4 (KCNA) -- The U.S. is going to additionally deploy U.S. air force in South Korea under the pretext of filling up a military vacuum on the Korean peninsula caused by the dispatch of the U.S. carrier kitty hawk to middle east in retaliation against the attacks on the U.S., according to Seoul-based radio No.1.
 The U.S. and the South Korean military authorities in a press release issued on Oct. 2 agreed to additionally beef up the U.S. air force in a bid to minimize the military vacuum on the Korean peninsula resulting from the redeployment of the carrier. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The South Korean Defense Ministry disclosed that some of the flying corps and naval force belonging to the kitty hawk which left Japan would remain in the west pacific ocean to strengthen the South Korea-U.S. "joint defensive posture." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This is a dangerous move to drive the situation on the Korean peninsula to the brink of war at any cost and the South Korean military authorities' support to the U.S. in its arms buildup is an act of chilling the Korean nation's ardent desire for reunification and a blatant challenge to its efforts to implement the June 15 joint declaration.

Inter-Korean talks open 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Kosong, October 4 (KCNA) -- Inter-Korean authorities' talks opened at Kumgangsan Hotel today to pep up the tourism of Mt. Kumgang, according to an agreement reached at the 5th inter-Korean ministerial talks.
 Kim Thaek Ryong, head of the delegation of the north side, recalled that the tourism has been underway in favor of promoting the reconciliation and unity of the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He said that pepping up the tourism is an important undertaking which has a positive impact on the overall north-south relations, calling for successfully holding the talks in conformity with the expectation and desire of the nation and its mission and duty to bring joy to all the fellow countrymen. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He stressed that both sides should actively promote the tourism of Mt. Kumgang, taking into consideration the actual possibility and conditions for pepping up it and advanced the north's proposal dealing with issues related to measures to be discussed and solved at the talks. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chief delegate of the south side spoke next. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The talks go on.
